De medio die ; equivalent in strietness to a medio statim die. The usual time for the Roman coena was the ninth hour, or three o’clock asternoon, in summer, and the tenth hour in winter. It was esteemed luxurious to sup earlier than this ; and an entertainment, therefore, begun before the usual time, and prolonged till late at night, was called by way of reproach convivium tempestivum, under which class the present one would fall. What is here stated respecting the horn-s of the Roman coena, applies, cf course, only to times of luxury and wealth.
